en people, and the challenge of trying to live a good life. The Charm of Wise Hesitancy explores the resurgence of interest in Talmudic stories in Israel and presents some of the most popular Talmudic stories in contemporary Israeli culture, as well as creative interpretations of those stories by Israeli writers, thereby providing readers with an opportunity to consider how these stories may be relevant to their own lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAggada. 0aOrthodox JudaismzIsraelxRelationsxNontraditional Jews. 0aSecularismzIsrael. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Talmud.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies ASPz978311071683240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811555340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618115553423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618115553.jpg  a978-3-11-071683-2  Religious Studies ASP  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK